A 26-year-old mother was arrested last Monday and appeared in court on charges of child abandonment after a baby was found dumped on Treadclay Road in Clayfield on 5 October. The article appeared in The Phoenix Tabloid on 8 October 2019. Phoenix SAPS communications officer, Captain L Naidoo, said that through intense investigations, the investigating officers Detective Warrant Officer C Naidoo and Sgt Mbanjwa both arrested the mother of the baby on Monday. <br />
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});<br /> “Sergeant Khanyile alleged that on arrival at the scene on 5 October, he noticed KZN VIP paramedics were already on the scene. “He was then informed by the paramedic that a baby was dropped off on Treadclay Road by an unknown Indian female as it was seen on CCTV footage.
The said female dropped the baby at the corner of the house and she went away. “The baby girl is about 27 days old. The baby was then handed over to Sgt Khanyile. She was wearing a yellow romper suit. The suspect was wearing black pants and a pink jacket. <br />
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});<br /> “The baby was taken to St Marys Hospital in Mariannhill for further care,” Cpt Naidoo added.